title: High Crop Production Index
description: In 2022, Senegal achieved a crop production index of 189.93, indicating significant agricultural productivity compared to the 2014-2016 baseline.

title: High Food Production Index
description: Senegal's food production index reached 177.49 in 2022, showing strong food production capabilities relative to the 2014-2016 baseline.

title: Gender Parity in Primary and Secondary Education
description: In 2021, Senegal had a gender parity index of 1.1759 for gross enrollment in primary and secondary education, indicating more females enrolled compared to males.

title: Low Women's Participation in Decision Making
description: Only 10.2% of women aged 15-49 in Senegal participated in key decision-making areas in 2019, highlighting a significant gender disparity.
